<title type="html"><![CDATA[SMB+Tetris+World Cup Mapper]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=86&amp;p=483#p483"><![CDATA[
Nintendo's Tetris uses the MMC1 only to swap CHR. It would probably be sickeningly easy to ROM-hack Tetris to MMC3 or even to CNROM (like Tengen's version) because it doesn't need to mix and match background and sprite CHR. When pulled out of the multicart and run in an emulator, does the Tetris part of the ROM exhibit MMC1-like or MMC3-like behavior in mapper writes?<br /><br />"DK" is Donkey Kong. What you're thinking of is "DH" for Duck Hunt.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Dec 08, 2004 5:43 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
